The Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission (EACC) has launched integrity center in learning institutions in Taita Taveta County in a bid to instill ethics and build good character students. Over 13 select schools are targeted in the one-week campaign in the region. Rose Mghoi, an EACC commissioner said the school outreach programme is designed to create awareness of integrity among students so as to nature and build a more responsible youth. Other 61 schools in the county had previously benefited from the programme. 